# Notes taken from Upload Vulnerabilties room on THM
# Part of Web fundamental Learning Path
# Remove hosts after room completion

For this room the hosts file must be updated - MUST have admin/root privilege
# Linux/Unix - /etc/hosts
# Windows - C:\Windows\System32\drivers\etc\hosts

Hosts - every time the room is accessed the host IP must be updated
# MACHINE_IP    overwrite.uploadvulns.thm shell.uploadvulns.thm java.uploadvulns.thm annex.uploadvulns.thm magic.uploadvulns.thm jewel.uploadvulns.thm demo.uploadvulns.thm

Reasons for why VM may not work
#1 Duplicate entries in host file
#2 VPN on top of THM VPN connection

Topics covered
# Overwriting Exisisting files on server
# Eploading & executing shells on server
# Bypassing Client-side filtering
# Bypassing various kinds of server-side filtering
# Fooling content type validation checks

Tools used
# Gobuster
# Burpsuite / OWASP ZAP
# Wappalyzer - browser extension

General
# Make the distinction between server & client-side filtering
# Take note of error messages based on actions
# Take note of server response 
# Burp suite repeater is a great way of testing responses 
